This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
9:02 AM Defendant James S Golembiewski not in court.  Attorney Aaron Thomas Vruwink in court for James S Golembiewski.  Attorney Jennifer C Zima in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Court orders warrant. No bond.
Email from CIB stating defendant just made an attempt to purchase a firearm.  Bond states NO POSSESSION OF FIREARMS.

3:45 PM Prosecuting attorney Austin M Mogard in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant James S Golembiewski in court. Attorney Aaron Thomas Vruwink in court for James S Golembiewski. 
Officer Klug is sworn in and testifies. Testifies to being an Officer with the Marshfield Police Department. Testifies to going into an establishment due to seeing a blue electric scooter that belonged to the defendant based on prior police contacts. Testifies to having contact w/ the defendant earlier that night. Witness identifies the defendant in court, court recognizes. Testifies to the defendant sitting at the bar when he arrived. Testifies to performing a PBT on the defendant. 

Attorney Mogard requests the court take Judicial Notice of an open case w/ a bond that was in full effect during this incident. 

Court finds probable cause to believe a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Bond is continued.
Status conference scheduled for August 8, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Court appoints Attorney Aaron Vruwink as counsel - Defendant must pay $50.00 per month toward attorney fees commencing September 1, 2022.
